oc:kn_13f5abd1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building debt schedules with interest expense linked to average debt balances" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Interest expense creates circularity: Interest → Net Income → Cash → Debt Balance → Interest. Enable iterative calculation (max 100 iterations, max change 0.001) and add a circuit breaker toggle in the Assumptions tab." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without handling circularity, Excel will either error or produce incorrect interest calculations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_45a4e5b0 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing projection formulas in either Office JS or Python/openpyxl environment" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "javascript" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Office JS: range.formulas = [["=D14*(1+Assumptions!$B$5)"]] — never use range.values for derived cells.
Python/openpyxl: ws["D15"] = "=D14*(1+Assumptions!$B$5)" — write formula strings, not computed results.""" .

oc:kn_523a1239 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After populating any statement — these are non-negotiable validation gates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Four cross-statement integrity checks must hold for every period: (1) Assets = Liabilities + Equity, (2) CF Ending Cash = BS Cash, (3) IS Net Income = CF starting Net Income, (4) Prior RE + NI + SBC - Dividends = BS Ending RE." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These four checks confirm the three statements are properly integrated. If any fails, the model is structurally broken." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_65df5e3a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the Checks/Audit tab for model validation" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Master Check: If all sections pass → "✓ ALL CHECKS PASS". If any section fails → "✗ ERRORS DETECTED - REVIEW BELOW".
Check sections: (1) Currency Consistency, (2) BS Integrity, (3) CF Integrity, (4) Retained Earnings, (5) Working Capital, (6) Debt Schedule, (6b) Equity Financing, (6c) NOL Schedule, (7) Scenario Hierarchy, (8) Formula Integrity, (9) Credit Metric Thresholds.""" .

oc:kn_685e1cff a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the Income Statement gross profit line" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Gross Profit must be calculated from Net Revenue (not Gross Revenue). Net Revenue = Gross Revenue - Returns - Allowances - Discounts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Using Gross Revenue overstates true top-line performance and inflates profitability metrics." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7db5e37d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When populating any projection or derived cell in the model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every projection cell, roll-forward, linkage, and subtotal MUST be an Excel formula — never a pre-computed hardcoded value. The ONLY cells containing hardcoded numbers are (1) historical actuals and (2) assumption drivers in the Assumptions tab." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The model must flex when scenarios toggle or assumptions change. Hardcodes break every downstream integrity check silently." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_7f79d254 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — never populate the entire model end-to-end without user confirmation at each statement boundary" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Map template tabs/sections → confirm with user. 2. Populate historicals → confirm values/periods. 3. Build IS projections → run subtotal checks, confirm. 4. Build BS → show balance check (Assets = L+E), confirm. 5. Build CF → show cash tie-out (CF ending cash = BS cash), confirm. 6. Final review." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Breaking at each statement catches errors early and prevents cascading mistakes across linked statements." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_94f14b37 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When entering data into an existing template" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never overwrite cells containing formulas unless intentionally replacing the formula. Never delete rows/columns without checking formula dependencies across all tabs." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overwriting formulas destroys the template's computational integrity and breaks cross-statement linkages." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c2ad20d1 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using Office JS / Excel Add-in environment for merged cells" ;
    oc:directiveContent "In Office JS, do NOT call .merge() then set .values on the merged range — it throws InvalidArgument. Instead write value to top-left cell alone, then merge + format the full range." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The merged range still reports pre-merge dimensions, causing dimension mismatch errors." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c47de176 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "Requires either Office JS (Excel Add-in) or Python with openpyxl for spreadsheet manipulation. Excel iterative calculation must be enabled for circular interest references." .

oc:kn_c945b485 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formatting any cell in the model, unless the template has its own color scheme" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Font color signals cell type (blue=input, black=formula, green=cross-tab link). Fill color signals location (dark blue=headers, light blue=column headers, grey/white=data, medium blue=checks). Use only 3 blues + 1 grey + white for fills." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent color coding enables instant visual identification of cell types and reduces errors in collaborative environments." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_feac6f92 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When Master Status shows errors" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Debug workflow: 1. Find red-highlighted sections on Checks tab. 2. Identify failing check category. 3. Navigate to source tab. 4. Fix underlying issue. 5. Return to Checks tab to verify resolution." ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_fed190ed a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building NOL/tax schedules" ;
    oc:directiveContent "NOL utilization is limited to 80% of EBT (post-2017 federal limit). Beginning NOL for Year 1 = 0 for new businesses. NOL balance must be non-negative. Tax expense = 0 when taxable income ≤ 0." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Post-2017 TCJA rules impose an 80% taxable income limitation on NOL utilization. Violating this produces incorrect tax calculations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

